// Best effort: derive view equality of underlying Vec<u8>.
    // The goal `r1.id == r2.id` (Vec spec equality) is not implied by
    // view equality of Vec<u8> in Verus's logic (Vec has no axiom relating
    // spec equality to view equality), so the synthetic check is unprovable
    // without an axiom that we are not permitted to introduce.
    assert(r1@.id == r1.id@);
    assert(r2@.id == r2.id@);
    assert(ep@.id == ep.id@);
